This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning problems in description logics, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely category. The paper also involves logical reasoning and complexity analysis, which are relevant to cs.LO. The use of axioms and fragments of ALC suggests that cs.DB and cs.DL are also relevant categories. Finally, the paper deals with the complexity of the satisfiability problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational complexity theory, making cs.CC a possible category as well.
